This paper discusses the challenge of providing explanations for AI systems, which is a common topic in the field of AI (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on the importance of making these explanations transparent and comprehensible to the user, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The methodology presented in the paper involves comparing alternative actions in plans, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the methodology in a new framework, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
